cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.CR

The paper proposes a measure to assess scientific impact, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. The evaluation of research impact of scholars and journals is related to digital libraries (cs.DL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of bibliometric measures such as h-index and ch-index is related to cybernetics (cs.CY) and security and privacy (cs.CR). Finally, the analysis of self-citations and their effect on rankings is related to social and information networks (cs.SI).
